refraction.book.misc.effects.content1=Red: burning entities and block. Cookable items will be cooked this way. With a certian alpha, red will also heat up furnaces. <br> Blue: gives various of potion effects to entities passing (mostly negative). Potion effects vary on beam alpha. <br> Green: Will apply bonemeal effect to growable blocks hit. Will also give players saturation.
refraction.book.misc.effects.content2=Cyan: Will pull entities. Creates light bridges on the exciter. Items can be pulled out of inventories. <br> Magenta: Will push entities away. Items can be pushed in inventories. <br> Yellow: Block breaking effect.
refraction.book.misc.effects.content3=Sky Blue: The gravity beam will completely nullify an entity's gravity. But that's not the interesting/dangerous part! The block a gravity beam touches will completely protect the block from taking any form of damage. Not only that, but it will also completely prevent players from interacting with the block.
refraction.book.misc.effects.content4=Orange: Will give a readstone signal to touching blocks and a speed effect to passing entities. <br> Pink: Block placing and animal breeding <br><br> Keep in mind that effects chance to trigger are based on alpha, also the strength of the effect depends on it. Alpha will fall off with distance!

